		</div>
	
	<div class="bbCodeBlock-content">
		
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			<s>How the fuck "equipment" = "industrial tools"? <img src="https://forums.sufficientvelocity.com/styles/sv_smiles/xenforo/FacePalm2.png" class="smilie" loading="lazy" alt=":facepalm:" title="Facepalm    :facepalm:" data-shortname=":facepalm:"> ...</s><br>
Wait, apparently there <i>is</i> suitable meaning. I just haven't encountered it before. Sorry, then.<br>
Then I need to look for WoG to confirm the right meaning in that case.<br>
<br>
<br>
It doesn't matter:<br>
<br>
So, even if they don't know how to produce it, but somehow got their hands on the piece of equ... accoutrement (I hope that word doesn't have wrong alternative meanings), Joe have the blueprint.<br>
<br>
<i><b><span style="font-size: 1.375rem">edit</span></b></i>:<br>
I can't find anything from LordR here, except the "yes, there could be some ork-tech in the databases" and "no Titans, but maybe some cars and walkers". The latter suggests that LordR's interpretation broader than <u>personal</u> equipment.<br>
Anyone willing to look on AO3 and/or Discord?
