		<article class="message-body js-selectToQuote">
			
				
			

			<div itemprop="text">
				
					<div class="bbWrapper"><blockquote data-attributes="member: 2871" data-quote="Sakuya's Butler" data-source="post: 20555398" class="bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch">
	
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-title">

			
				<a href="https://forums.sufficientvelocity.com/threads/brocktons-celestial-forge-worm-jumpchain.70036/page-649#post-20555398" class="bbCodeBlock-sourceJump" rel="nofollow" data-xf-click="attribution" data-content-selector="#post-20555398">Sakuya's Butler said:</a>
			
		</div>
	
	<div class="bbCodeBlock-content">
		
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			TMK the Anti-Spiral doesn't exist in Worms' specific subset of dimensions within the multiverse.
		</div>
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink"><a role="button" tabindex="0">Click to expand...</a></div>

<div class="bbCodeBlock-shrinkLink"><a>Click to shrink...</a></div>
	</div>
</blockquote>Joe would cause the Antispiral to manifest if he went beyond Beastman Arc levels of Spiral.<br>




<blockquote data-attributes="member: 2871" data-quote="Sakuya's Butler" data-source="post: 20555398" class="bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch is-expandable">
	
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-title">

			
				<a href="https://forums.sufficientvelocity.com/threads/brocktons-celestial-forge-worm-jumpchain.70036/page-649#post-20555398" class="bbCodeBlock-sourceJump" rel="nofollow" data-xf-click="attribution" data-content-selector="#post-20555398">Sakuya's Butler said:</a>
			
		</div>
	
	<div class="bbCodeBlock-content">
		
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			OTOH, Joe's one <u>dense</u> idiot, not seeing the forest for the trees, so yes, his mentality IS a problem.<br>
<br>
<i>Especially</i> as he's already been GIVEN the intimate knowledge, which he knows at a fundamental, soul-deep level, that acting like Kamina or Simon....<br>
<br>
<b>WORKS</b>.
		</div>
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink"><a role="button" tabindex="0">Click to expand...</a></div>

<div class="bbCodeBlock-shrinkLink"><a>Click to shrink...</a></div>
	</div>
</blockquote>I mean, that's a pretty recent occurrence, so can't blame him for not following that.<br>




<blockquote data-attributes="member: 2871" data-quote="Sakuya's Butler" data-source="post: 20555398" class="bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch is-expandable">
	
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-title">

			
				<a href="https://forums.sufficientvelocity.com/threads/brocktons-celestial-forge-worm-jumpchain.70036/page-649#post-20555398" class="bbCodeBlock-sourceJump" rel="nofollow" data-xf-click="attribution" data-content-selector="#post-20555398">Sakuya's Butler said:</a>
			
		</div>
	
	<div class="bbCodeBlock-content">
		
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			Its like...<br>
<br>
Someone being given the entire combine powerset of the Justice League AND the Avengers...<br>
<br>
Then ignoring the obvious bonuses they could leverage together, to instead tinker around as Tony Stark and only briefly using the superficial 'tip of the iceberg' level abilities, and not really getting into the meat of his powers.<br>
<br>
(Doesn't help either that he truly cannot blame lack of time, as he has, iirc, knowledge of how to create a DBZ Hyperbolic Time Chamber)<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I like the story, I really do. I'm just waiting with relish the moment Joe realizes he fucked up horribly ages ago, prior to March EVER showing up, and even back then could have gone to the mat against Endbringers and won. All those deaths, maimings, misunderstandings, resources lost, enemies made, opportunities squandered...<br>
<br>
Because he wasn't truly thinking outside the box.<br>
<br>
I'm going to enjoy that moment.
		</div>
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink"><a role="button" tabindex="0">Click to expand...</a></div>

<div class="bbCodeBlock-shrinkLink"><a>Click to shrink...</a></div>
	</div>
</blockquote>Big disagreement on how obvious things are. Joe doesn't have the meta knowledge of his passenger, and even if he did, Magic-parahuman equivalence muddies the waters quite a bit. The endbringers aren't a big threat, but still a sizable threat to Joe. As for hyperbolic time chambers, he does have 24rd century (Star Trek) physics to give him the theory behind that, but it isn't anything obvious. He doesn't have DBZ tech or anything.<br>
<br>
Also this idea that Joe could have killed the endbringers and fixed the world before the ABB started up is ridiculous, to the point where I question what story you've been reading. Sure, Joe's let some stuff that he could've theoretically stopped had he seen it coming, but again, no meta knowledge.<br>
<br>
Also this "I shall enjoy watching Joe suffer" shit is really weird-champ, personally.<br>
<br>
EDIT: As Cerriwen pointed out, killing the Endbringers isn't a good idea. He'd have to kill all 20 once he started, and who knows how the timing might change, or how BB might be affected by constantly being the target thanks to Eidolon, or hell even Scion deciding that Joe is a system threat and snapping out of his Depression????</div>
				
			</div>

			
	
	
		
	

