	<div class="bbCodeBlock-content">
		
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			Yep. With meta-knowledge he could've deal with Zion already.<br>
1) Call Bead - Sting.<br>
2) "Hello, Sting, wanna get some [DATA]? ... Then you need to do that ..."<br>
3) Call Bead - Zion.<br>
4) Profit.
		</div>
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink"><a role="button" tabindex="0">Click to expand...</a></div>

<div class="bbCodeBlock-shrinkLink"><a>Click to shrink...</a></div>
	</div>
</blockquote>I mean, let's just quick read some WOG about Call Beads/Gems.<br>




<blockquote data-attributes="" data-quote="" data-source="" class="bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch is-expandable">
	
	<div class="bbCodeBlock-content">
		
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			Connecting a call bead to a specific entity is a very different case than the generic beads that Joe has been producing. Connected call beads allow the person who activates them to use one of the abilities of the entity they're connected to, but the strength of the effect is based on your own magical skill. Quality boosts would change this, but larger beads would probably create situations where you had more options for effects and longer durations rather than just overwhelming power.
		</div>
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink"><a role="button" tabindex="0">Click to expand...</a></div>

<div class="bbCodeBlock-shrinkLink"><a>Click to shrink...</a></div>
	</div>
</blockquote>Sting Gems would be WMDs, essentially. He could've wiped out the ABB, wiped out the Endbringers, bring enough of them and deal with Scion.<br>
Now I'm tempted to write an omake where Joe is given all this knowledge about Worm and Wards during his trigger event <img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" class="smilie smilie--sprite smilie--sprite66" alt=":)" title="Smile    :)" loading="lazy" data-shortname=":)"><br>
