	<div class="message-userContent lbContainer js-lbContainer " data-lb-id="post-20558368" data-lb-caption-desc="The Shallow ┬Ę Jun 28, 2021 at 8:16 PM">

		

		<article class="message-body js-selectToQuote">
			
				
			

			<div itemprop="text">
				
					<div class="bbWrapper"><blockquote data-attributes="member: 64886" data-quote="Cerridwen" data-source="post: 20558332" class="bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch">
	
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-title">

			
				<a href="https://forums.sufficientvelocity.com/threads/brocktons-celestial-forge-worm-jumpchain.70036/page-649#post-20558332" class="bbCodeBlock-sourceJump" rel="nofollow" data-xf-click="attribution" data-content-selector="#post-20558332">Cerridwen said:</a>
			
		</div>
	
	<div class="bbCodeBlock-content">
		
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			If they're based on <i>his </i>magic ability, wouldn't they be inferior to the actual Sting? I don't think Joe has enough magical energy to create an omnidimensional attack. In DnD terms he's casting it at a lower spell slot, with a lower modifier, I suppose
		</div>
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink"><a role="button" tabindex="0">Click to expand...</a></div>

<div class="bbCodeBlock-shrinkLink"><a>Click to shrink...</a></div>
	</div>
</blockquote>Yeah, probably. Most his quality perks don't apply, since they aren't magic based, but Do One Thing At A Time is still a thing, and even then he could find a way to redline it through Magitech, no?<br>




<blockquote data-attributes="member: 42519" data-quote="Koraan" data-source="post: 20558347" class="bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch is-expandable">
	
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-title">

			
				<a href="https://forums.sufficientvelocity.com/threads/brocktons-celestial-forge-worm-jumpchain.70036/page-649#post-20558347" class="bbCodeBlock-sourceJump" rel="nofollow" data-xf-click="attribution" data-content-selector="#post-20558347">Koraan said:</a>
			
		</div>
	
	<div class="bbCodeBlock-content">
		
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			Heh. Nah. That's easier, quickier and smarter than just throwing grenades (even peally advanced) at Zion's avatar.<br>
As we saw when March used her power, Sting's power can turn Call Bead into a "window", portal to the place with which Bead connected. So, instead of fighting with Zion, Joe could, with Sting's help, directly attack his main body.
		</div>
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink"><a role="button" tabindex="0">Click to expand...</a></div>

<div class="bbCodeBlock-shrinkLink"><a>Click to shrink...</a></div>
	</div>
</blockquote>Well it's gonna be a bit hard to just destroy him with grenades, but generally I agree. I hadn't even thought of that! Then again, those rifts are unstable and very temporary, but the big Advantage of Sting is it's weight with Fate magic. It's the unstoppable attack of an eldritch entity. Scion has no way to counter it, either way.</div>
				
			</div>

			
	
	
		
	

