		<article class="message-body js-selectToQuote">
			
				
			

			<div itemprop="text">
				
					<div class="bbWrapper">There are issues with Joe using wmds already, they already used nuclear weapons on behemoth and the result was so catastrophic that countries worldwide even those with nuclear weapons decided it was such a bad idea that nuclearly armed countries decided to simply not used them ever again<br>
<br>
whatever Joe could unleash to kill the endbringers is potentially a horrible idea<br>
<br>
vortex grenades for instance would likely be recorded, with several pre-cogs ant thinkers examining, only to then be corrupted by Tzeech and successfully open a warp tear on earth, or using sorcery to corrupt shards and potentially even scion and the endbringers<br>
<br>
Korn might lead brutes into berserker modes and even activating the warriors rampage, Nurgle would likely thrive with Bonesaw as she creates several Nurgalite plagues and overwhelms Jack with some sort of anti-scrying-mental-disease (I'm sure nurgle has this in his arsenal somewhere) causing a plague scenario, which ironically I haven't seen in any worm fics<br>
<br>
this issue is compounded as places that experienced warp activity are more likely to experience again as the border between worlds if made thinner, meaning ghosts and even demonic apparitions are likely to occur in Brockton bay, given that demons can very much be summoned individually as demon hosts<br>
<br>
there are very few instances where messing with the warp in any way is desirable, and the end bringers might legitimately not cross that trashold</div>
				
			</div>

			
	
	
		
	

