	<div class="message-userContent lbContainer js-lbContainer " data-lb-id="post-20559439" data-lb-caption-desc="prussiangrandier ┬Ę Jun 28, 2021 at 10:27 PM">

		

		<article class="message-body js-selectToQuote">
			
				
			

			<div itemprop="text">
				
					<div class="bbWrapper">I understand that that is a risk but in a story that is a risk worth considering, the weakening of the material border is legitimately a danger to the world that cannot be overstated, there is a non-zero chance that Zion will intervene with maximum brutality and quarantine the entirety of Brockton bay into a Gray boy bubble<br>
<br>
admittedly the chance of that is incredibly small, but it is present, since if they know what the imaterium is they also know about the dangers that dwell in it<br>
<br>
the imaterium technically does contain infinite energy, and since resistance to the warp is a wisdom saving throw and the entity will according to WOG kill each other if they believe that will lead to infinite energy its likely that several entities were corrupted by chaos and or the warp itself, if they knew what it was of course<br>
<br>
again the chances of such are small but not so small as to be completely dismissible to someone in universe<br>
<br>
conversion beamers are likely to have no more effect than conventional fission, I can however see graviton weapons being capable of destroying them, since the endbringers have a density close to the schwarzschild radius so a sufficiently powerful graviton weapon would theoretically be capable of harming them by causing them to collapse into a black hole<br>
<br>
that is until you realize they have defenses and can control their own mass, and that even if you succeed, you just created a black hole, defeating the whole point of this thought exercise<br>
<br>
The endbringers are that powerfully offensively all said and done; they are extraordinarily hard to deal with, but the truth of the matter is that they are much stronger defensively than offensively, you can destroy them with a planetary level attack, but those destroy the connection to the core, which opens the possibility that they could be restored by the entities or even other endbringers<br>
<br>
if this was another version of the forge, I could see the evil containment wave working, or some legendary Pok├®mon. But that is still far beyond what Joe can create <br>
<br>
I legitimately believe that Joe is above the triumvirate, with maybe some difficulty because of eidolons versatility<br>
<br>
overall, It's still a problem without a straightforward solution</div>
				
			</div>

			
	
	
		
	

