		<article class="message-body js-selectToQuote">
			
				
			

			<div itemprop="text">
				
					<div class="bbWrapper"><blockquote data-attributes="member: 26271" data-quote="prussiangrandier" data-source="post: 20559439" class="bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch is-expandable">
	
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-title">

			
				<a href="https://forums.sufficientvelocity.com/threads/brocktons-celestial-forge-worm-jumpchain.70036/page-649#post-20559439" class="bbCodeBlock-sourceJump" rel="nofollow" data-xf-click="attribution" data-content-selector="#post-20559439">prussiangrandier said:</a>
			
		</div>
	
	<div class="bbCodeBlock-content">
		
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent ">
			I understand that that is a risk but in a story that is a risk worth considering, the weakening of the material border is legitimately a danger to the world that cannot be overstated, there is a non-zero chance that Zion will intervene with maximum brutality and quarantine the entirety of Brockton bay into a Gray boy bubble<br>
<br>
admittedly the chance of that is incredibly small, but it is present, since if they know what the imaterium is they also know about the dangers that dwell in it<br>
<br>
the imaterium technically does contain infinite energy, and since resistance to the warp is a wisdom saving throw and the entity will according to WOG kill each other if they believe that will lead to infinite energy its likely that several entities were corrupted by chaos and or the warp itself, if they knew what it was of course
		</div>
		<div class="bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink"><a role="button" tabindex="0">Click to expand...</a></div>

<div class="bbCodeBlock-shrinkLink"><a>Click to shrink...</a></div>
	</div>
</blockquote>I would like to point out that this is not the Warhammer universe.  The Immaterium doesn't exist here and will never exist.  There will be no Warp corruption as a result, even if Joe throws around Warp Grenades like Oprah.  The Entities have no knowledge of the Warp or the Immaterium, because, as stated, it doesn't exist.  It's not in this multiverse.<br>
<br>
The Warp Grenades that Joe can create will not connect to the Warp, they will simply be semi-mobile dimensional tears.</div>
				
